<section class="app-page-shell about-page-shell">
    <section class="app-page-header about-page-hero">
        <div class="about-page-copy">
            <p class="about-page-eyebrow">About HelloUniversity</p>
            <h1>Digital academic platform for school and higher education workflows.</h1>
            <p class="about-page-lead">
                HelloUniversity is not a university itself. It is a digital academic platform designed to support school and higher education workflows such as classes, assessments, communication, and learning management.
            </p>

            <div class="about-page-actions">
                <a href="/lessons" class="about-page-btn about-page-btn-primary">Browse Lessons</a>
                <a href="/contact" class="about-page-btn about-page-btn-secondary">Contact Support</a>
            </div>

            <ul class="about-page-role-list" aria-label="Primary audiences">
                <li><span class="material-icons" aria-hidden="true">school</span> Students</li>
                <li><span class="material-icons" aria-hidden="true">co_present</span> Teachers</li>
                <li><span class="material-icons" aria-hidden="true">admin_panel_settings</span> Academic teams</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <aside class="about-page-focus-card">
            <p class="about-page-card-label">Platform Focus</p>
            <h2>Built around practical academic work</h2>
            <ul class="about-page-focus-list">
                <li>Structured lesson tracks and companion reading paths</li>
                <li>Role-aware classroom tools for students, teachers, and admins</li>
                <li>Operational flows for classes, assessments, communication, and attendance</li>
                <li>Support pages that keep navigation and discovery clear</li>
            </ul>
        </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="about-page-grid">
        <article class="app-panel about-page-panel">
            <div class="about-page-section-heading">
                <p class="about-page-section-eyebrow">Mission</p>
                <h2>Reduce friction in learning and classroom operations</h2>
            </div>
            <p>
                HelloUniversity is designed to make academic work easier to navigate. The platform connects learning content, class management, assessments, communication, and support flows so users spend less time switching contexts and more time moving through the work that matters.
            </p>
            <div class="about-page-mini-grid">
                <article class="about-page-mini-card">
                    <h3>Learning first</h3>
                    <p>Lessons, companion reading, and public content are organized so users can find relevant material quickly.</p>
                </article>
                <article class="about-page-mini-card">
                    <h3>Operational clarity</h3>
                    <p>Shared navigation, focused dashboards, and clearer page-level structure reduce avoidable UI friction.</p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </article>

        <aside class="app-panel app-panel-muted about-page-panel about-page-side-panel">
            <p class="about-page-section-eyebrow">Vision</p>
            <h2>A clearer academic experience across the whole product</h2>
            <p>
                The long-term direction is a system where lessons, class workflows, analytics, and support content all feel like part of one consistent platform rather than separate tools.
            </p>
        </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="about-page-section">
        <div class="about-page-section-heading">
            <p class="about-page-section-eyebrow">Product History</p>
            <h2>From HelloGrade to HelloUniversity</h2>
            <p>The platform started with a narrower job, then expanded as the academic workflows around it grew.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-page-history-grid">
            <article class="app-panel about-page-history-card">
                <span class="material-icons about-page-pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">grading</span>
                <h3>HelloGrade</h3>
                <p>
                    The product was originally created as <strong>HelloGrade</strong>, a grading portal focused on helping schools and teachers manage grade-related workflows more clearly.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="app-panel about-page-history-card">
                <span class="material-icons about-page-pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">school</span>
                <h3>Expanded Academic Platform Scope</h3>
                <p>
                    As the platform matured, it expanded beyond grading into a broader academic platform with lessons, quizzes, classroom tools, communication workflows, attendance, and academic support content.
                </p>
            </article>

            <article class="app-panel about-page-history-card">
                <span class="material-icons about-page-pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">account_balance</span>
                <h3>HelloUniversity</h3>
                <p>
                    The rebrand to <strong>HelloUniversity</strong> reflects that wider scope: a digital academic platform for school and higher education workflows such as classes, assessments, communication, and learning management, not a university itself.
                </p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-page-section">
        <div class="about-page-section-heading">
            <p class="about-page-section-eyebrow">Core Pillars</p>
            <h2>What the platform is built to support</h2>
            <p>The current product direction centers on five connected pillars.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="about-page-pillar-grid">
            <article class="app-panel about-page-pillar-card">
                <span class="material-icons about-page-pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">account_tree</span>
                <h3>Academic Management</h3>
                <p>Academic terms, classes, courses, sections, and student class membership that help institutions organize academic operations clearly.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="app-panel about-page-pillar-card">
                <span class="material-icons about-page-pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">menu_book</span>
                <h3>Learning Management</h3>
                <p>Learning materials, quizzes, online activities, assignments, and submissions that support teaching and learning in one digital environment.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="app-panel about-page-pillar-card">
                <span class="material-icons about-page-pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">campaign</span>
                <h3>Communication and Engagement</h3>
                <p>Announcements, reminders, and class updates that improve coordination, keep learners informed, and reduce missed academic information.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="app-panel about-page-pillar-card">
                <span class="material-icons about-page-pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">grading</span>
                <h3>Grading and Student Academic Access</h3>
                <p>Grade encoding, computation, released grade viewing, optional score breakdowns, controlled release, and authorized grade editing.</p>
            </article>

            <article class="app-panel about-page-pillar-card">
                <span class="material-icons about-page-pillar-icon" aria-hidden="true">insights</span>
                <h3>Monitoring and Intelligent Support</h3>
                <p>Academic monitoring, progress tracking, and selected AI-assisted support that help faculty respond more efficiently to student needs.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="about-page-section">
